<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="M" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Mournful" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Mournful,</orth> 1) expressing sorrow: <cit><quote>her m. hymns,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 102.10" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 102, 10</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>m. epitaphs,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 4.1.209" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado IV, 1, 209</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the m. crocodile,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.1.226" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 1, 226</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>my m. tears,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.340" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 340</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>m. weeds,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tit 5.3.196" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. V, 3, 196</bibl></cit> (Q<hi rend="sub">1</hi> <emph>mourning</emph>). <cit><quote>m. bell,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tit 5.3.196" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. V, 3, 196</bibl></cit><lb />2) causing sorrow: <cit><quote>his m. death,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.2.16" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A II, 2, 16</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>